  "body": "I set up the repo today, and tried to run the tests as instructed in the README, however, it seems that the `requests` library is needed for that. Shouldn't this be added to some kind of dependency tracking list? \r\n\r\nThere doesn't seem to any in the project, and I'm definitely a Python amateur, but shouldn't a `requirements.txt`be used in this case? Looking a bit more into it, it looks like to specify some dependencies in `setup.py` (and [many other ways](https://dephell.readthedocs.io/cmd-deps-convert.html) to do it) It guess it depends where `pytest` looks?\r\n\r\nAlso we want to avoid to have `requests` as an install dependencies if it is only used for tests.\r\n\r\nA bit unrelated, but I also ran into another issue while running the tests: https://github.com/ethereum/execution-specs/pull/315#issuecomment-914467970",
