    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Felt stupid for a minute, as both `pip install -e .[doc,lint,test]` and `pip install -e .[test]` both result in \"-e option requires 1 argument\".\r\n\r\nTurns out in bash, `[]` are [wildcard syntax](https://tldp.org/LDP/GNU-Linux-Tools-Summary/html/x11655.htm).\r\n\r\nSo the proper bash-compatible command ends up being `pip install -e \".[doc,lint,test]\". I'll open a pull-request to fix.\r\n\r\nI'll setup `tox`, I (foolishly) assumed it was a documentation toolchain!",
